General.Name: ModivCare Inc
General.Description: ModivCare Inc., a technology-enabled healthcare services company, provides a suite of integrated supportive care solutions for public and private payors and their members in the United States. It operates through four segments: Non-Emergency Medical Transportation, Personal Care Services, Monitoring, and Corporate and Other. The Non-Emergency Medical Transportation segment offers risk underwriting, contact center management, network credentialing, claims management, and non-emergency medical transport management services for Medicaid or Medicare eligible members. The Personal Care Services segment provides in-home personal care services, such as bathing, personal hygiene, grooming, oral care, dressing, medication reminders, meal planning, preparation and feeding, housekeeping, transportation services, prescription reminders, assistance with dressing and ambulation services, home health aides, and nurses primarily to Medicaid patients in need of care monitoring and assistance in performing daily living activities in the home setting, including senior citizens and disabled adults. The Monitoring segment offers in-home clinical monitoring and quality improvement services, including personal emergency response systems, vitals monitoring devices, and relationship-based care and data-driven patient engagement solutions. The Corporate and Other segment maintains a network of community-based clinicians that deliver in-home and on-site services. It serves federal, state, and local government agencies, managed care organizations, commercial insurers, private individuals, and health systems. The company was formerly known as The Providence Service Corporation and changed its name to ModivCare Inc. in January 2021. ModivCare Inc. was incorporated in 1996 and is headquartered in Denver, Colorado.
